  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Village Partnership supports individuals in identifying their most pressing needs, and trains communities to make sound decisions and take action towards change. 

Far removed from the technology, commerce, and infrastructure of modern cities, many people living in remote areas throughout developing countries live traditional lifestyles characterized by acute poverty. The cycle of poverty for the people in these communities is perpetual and is due to a combination of several factors including poor infrastructure, lack of education and limited sources of food and income. Through Village Partnerships, spiritual growth, food security, education, agribusiness and community health are addressed in a coordinated way to bring lasting improvement.</narrative>
  </description>
